  "title": "Assistant Project Manager / Project Manager (ID)",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Assistant Project Manager / Project Manager (ID)</strong></h2>\n<h2>- Corporate office renovation, F&amp;B or Medical</h2>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p>\n<p>Reporting to Senior Manager.</p>\n<p>Account Servicing: Obtain design requirements, present design proposal, prepare costing and quotation, negotiate and clinch deal.</p>\n<p>Review drawings to ensure compliance with client and authority requirements.</p>\n<p>Manage project Processes from initiating, planning, executing, monitoring &amp; controlling, to final closing.</p>\n<p>Manage full Scope of commercial interior design &amp; construction projects, including architectural, M&amp;E, and submission works.</p>\n<p>Manage project Schedule to ensure Project are delivered on time.</p>\n<p>Manage Cost and budget, including reviewing contractor contracts, and controlling expenses.</p>\n<p>Maintain Quality, including conducting factory checks, job site housekeeping, and adhering to safety standards.</p>\n<p>Optimize Resource utilization, including manpower and materials management.</p>\n<p>Develop effective Communications between internal Staff &amp; Management, Contractors, Clients, Agents, and Authorities, including conducting meetings, preparing and presenting project status updates &amp; reports.</p>\n<p>Identify Project Risks and prepare mitigation measures.</p>\n<p>Prepare and complete documentation as required by relevant stakeholders.</p>\n<p>Manage defect servicing and maintenance works.</p>\n<p>Any other tasks as may be required.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Email : HR@ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n<p>Familiar with at least 2 out of 3 key trades, Corporate office renovation, F&amp;B or Medical industry</p>\n<p>Well versed in technical processes in Architectural and M&amp;E scope of works.</p>\n<p>Resourceful with good knowledge in materials and pricing.</p>\n<p>Able to work under pressure in a fast-paced challenging environment.</p>\n<p>Excellent problem analyzing and solving skills.</p>\n<p>A team player with strong individual drive, sense of responsibility and task ownership.</p>\n<p>Demonstrates good interpersonal and leadership qualities.</p>\n<p>Experience working with all levels of Clients, Contractors, Authorities, Agents and Landlords etc.</p>\n<p>Able to do night job if required.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Email : HR@ppsjob.com.sg</strong></p>",
